As a database administrator, I want to process deletions from a specific date, so that old transaction data is cleaned up.
As a UI designer, I want to redesign the resources page, so that it matches new Broker styles and is responsive.
As a reporting analyst, I want to send user testing reports to agencies, so that they can review testing results.
As a system administrator, I want to configure New Relic monitoring for applications, so that we can monitor application performance.
As a data engineer, I want to sync D1 file generation with FPDS data load, so that files are generated only when FPDS data is updated.
As a database developer, I want to update SQL code for better clarity, so that stored procedures are more maintainable.
As a data analyst, I want to add PPoPCode cases to derivation logic, so that special cases like wildcards and foreign locations are handled.
As a data quality specialist, I want to derive FundingAgencyCode, so that data quality is improved when codes are missing.
As a UX designer, I want to launch design iterations for different pages, so that UI improvements can be tested and approved.
As a developer, I want to enhance logging for submissions, so that we have more detailed logs for troubleshooting.
As a website user, I want to get published FABS files for my agency, so that I can access the latest published data.
As a testing coordinator, I want to schedule user testing with advanced notice, so that testers are prepared.
As a database architect, I want to ensure proper indexing for domain models, so that query performance is optimized.
As a FABS administrator, I want to update submissions when publishStatus changes, so that records reflect current status.
As a system integrator, I want to add GTAS windows to the database, so that integration periods are properly tracked.
As a data loader, I want to load historical FPDS data from a given year, so that historical records are available.
As a validation engineer, I want to update validation rules, so that data validation remains accurate and up-to-date.
As a file manager, I want to manage and cache D File generation requests, so that performance is optimized.
As a database optimizer, I want to optimize handling of large numbers of flexfields, so that storage is used efficiently.
As a data validator, I want to validate FABS files against schema, so that data conforms to expected formats.
